The article discusses an executive order issued by President Obama to establish a federal earthquake risk management standard. The order aims to enhance the security and resilience of the nation against earthquakes and promote public safety, economic strength, and national security. The order requires each federal agency responsible for constructing or leasing buildings to ensure that they are designed and constructed to meet earthquake-resistant codes and standards. The order also establishes guidelines and responsibilities for agencies to comply with the standard and provides exemptions under certain circumstances. The order revokes previous executive orders related to seismic safety of federal buildings. The order applies to buildings within the United States and its territories and possessions.